OL,6,FPC Dan McNary said: "Royle had been
OL,7,Fgiven every opportunity to engage in
OL,8,Frehabilitation and was subject to
OL,9,Fstrict measures designed to reduce the
OL,10,Frisk of him reoffending.
OL,12,F"He has been unable to adhere to these
OL,13,Frestrictions and has demonstrated a
OL,14,Fclear determination to access the
OL,15,Finternet, in order to contact and
OL,16,Fabuse children.
